# Encrypted bootstrap env template
#
# Create your own encrypted file named:
#   bootstrap.private.env.age
#
# Content before encryption should be a simple shell env file, for example:
#   GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_xxx
#
# Encrypt example with age-plugin-yubikey recipient:
#   age -r <your-age1yubikey-recipient> -o bootstrap.private.env.age bootstrap.private.env
#
# For this repo bootstrap, YubiKey identity is expected at:
#   ~/.config/age/yubikey-identities.txt
#
# Software age keys are intentionally not used by default.
# To allow fallback (not recommended), set:
#   ALLOW_SOFTWARE_AGE_KEYS=1
#
# IMPORTANT:
# - Never commit plaintext bootstrap.private.env
# - Commit only bootstrap.private.env.age
